1
00:00:51,399 --> 00:00:51,719
Hi.

2
00:00:52,079 --> 00:00:52,479
It turns out

3
00:00:52,479 --> 00:00:54,880
that the one who killed you two is the young master's family.

4
00:00:54,880 --> 00:00:56,600
The young master doesn't want to be separated from the young lady.

5
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:59,000
His family forced him to drink hard liquor,

6
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:01,479
and wanted to take him away when he was asleep.

7
00:01:01,479 --> 00:01:03,320
It's such a boring plot again.

8
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:04,799
What are you doing?

9
00:01:05,359 --> 00:01:05,960
What are you doing?

10
00:01:07,560 --> 00:01:09,280
I was forced to do this.

11
00:01:09,680 --> 00:01:11,359
Can't you see I'm being controlled?

12
00:01:12,439 --> 00:01:13,480
Don't push your luck.

13
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:14,680
It's the formation.

14
00:01:14,799 --> 00:01:16,079
I have no choice.

15
00:01:18,719 --> 00:01:21,439
[The mission needs you to help him sober up.]

16
00:01:21,439 --> 00:01:23,359
[To promote the relationship between them.]

17
00:01:24,519 --> 00:01:25,920
It's so cliché.

18
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:27,799
Come on.

19
00:01:28,400 --> 00:01:29,719
There are hangover remedies on the table.

20
00:01:29,719 --> 00:01:30,640
Help me take them.

21
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:33,280
The hangover tea works the fastest.

22
00:01:34,239 --> 00:01:35,359
After I drink it,

23
00:01:37,959 --> 00:01:38,799
am I sober?

24
00:01:44,079 --> 00:01:45,239
There's water,

25
00:01:45,239 --> 00:01:45,799
a handkerchief,

26
00:01:46,159 --> 00:01:47,079
an antidote,

27
00:01:47,079 --> 00:01:47,760
and fruits.

28
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:49,719
Why did you use this method?

29
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:51,920
It's so convenient.

30
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:54,239
Fine.

31
00:01:54,719 --> 00:01:56,680
Since you disobey the plot,

32
00:01:56,680 --> 00:01:58,879
I'll do what I want.

33
00:02:03,439 --> 00:02:04,480
[The next day,]

34
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:07,239
[the young lady's family found you.]

35
00:02:07,239 --> 00:02:09,120
[Her father was furious]

36
00:02:09,120 --> 00:02:11,120
[when he knew you were alone in a room.]

37
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:13,080
and was willing to kill you

38
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:15,159
to separate you two.

39
00:02:20,599 --> 00:02:23,400
It's a sin for you to stay with this bad guy for a night.

40
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:24,680
I know you are young.

41
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:26,439
If you are willing to go back with me

42
00:02:26,439 --> 00:02:28,439
and marry a good man,

43
00:02:28,439 --> 00:02:30,280
I will kill him today

44
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:31,840
and let you go.

45
00:02:31,919 --> 00:02:33,599
If you are still stubborn,

46
00:02:33,599 --> 00:02:35,719
I can only kill you for the sake of righteousness

47
00:02:35,719 --> 00:02:37,479
to rectify the family rules.

48
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:38,120
Ah!

49
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:39,080
Old man,

50
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:41,599
who says women must be docile

51
00:02:41,599 --> 00:02:42,560
and marry well?

52
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:43,919
As his father,

53
00:02:44,159 --> 00:02:45,759
you're so rigid,

54
00:02:45,759 --> 00:02:46,439
and pedantic.

55
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:49,599
Finally, you said something sensible.

56
00:02:49,599 --> 00:02:51,360
I've always been sensible.

57
00:02:51,599 --> 00:02:52,400
Your Highness,

58
00:02:52,599 --> 00:02:54,120
you're really smooth-talking,

59
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:55,199
always so eloquent.

60
00:02:55,199 --> 00:02:56,879
With such a sharp tongue,

61
00:02:56,879 --> 00:02:58,000
you might as well think about

62
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:59,520
how to break the current situation.

63
00:02:59,520 --> 00:03:00,280
One problem at a time.

64
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:01,000
One step at a time.

65
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,360
Just solve the problem.

66
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:03,240
Oh,

67
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:05,800
I'm still here.

68
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:08,080
How come you two are talking?

69
00:03:08,319 --> 00:03:09,919
I heard that old man

70
00:03:10,159 --> 00:03:11,879
said we must write

71
00:03:11,879 --> 00:03:13,840
a moving happy ending

72
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:14,599
to break the formation.

73
00:03:15,319 --> 00:03:16,520
In my opinion,

74
00:03:17,039 --> 00:03:18,479
if I choose to die for you,

75
00:03:18,759 --> 00:03:20,080
I'm sure I can succeed.

76
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:21,840
Don't be self-satisfied.

77
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:23,120
If you die,

78
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:24,520
it's not a perfect ending.

79
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:26,479
Then let's make a bet.

80
00:03:27,719 --> 00:03:28,520
Old man,

81
00:03:28,879 --> 00:03:30,599
you young man

82
00:03:30,599 --> 00:03:32,560
is so impolite.

83
00:03:33,240 --> 00:03:34,879
I'm willing to die for Meng Li

84
00:03:34,879 --> 00:03:36,919
to keep her safe.

85
00:03:38,319 --> 00:03:38,879
Good.

86
00:03:39,199 --> 00:03:39,759
Good.

87
00:03:55,919 --> 00:03:57,280
You always think

88
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:59,719
self-sacrifice is the right choice.

89
00:04:00,159 --> 00:04:01,599
If the setting is wrong,

90
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,280
how can there be a right answer?

91
00:04:08,919 --> 00:04:10,280
The grudges

92
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:12,759
are shackles imposed on others.

93
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:14,680
If these trivial matters

94
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:16,639
can determine others' lives,

95
00:04:16,919 --> 00:04:18,920
then it's impossible for me.

96
00:04:19,519 --> 00:04:21,680
Don't expect me to compromise this time.

97
00:04:27,839 --> 00:04:28,720
Fine.

98
00:04:29,720 --> 00:04:30,519
Fine.

99
00:04:30,759 --> 00:04:31,839
In a hundred years,

100
00:04:31,839 --> 00:04:33,000
you're the first

101
00:04:33,240 --> 00:04:35,040
to make such a choice.

102
00:04:35,399 --> 00:04:36,680
This is the result

103
00:04:37,319 --> 00:04:39,519
of your refusal to compromise.

104
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:47,160
Meng Li.

105
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:48,680
What happened to her?

106
00:04:48,959 --> 00:04:51,160
You failed to give me the results I wanted.

107
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:52,360
I won't tell you

108
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:53,560
what you want to know.

109
00:04:53,920 --> 00:04:56,399
[But I can give you a chance.]

110
00:04:56,639 --> 00:04:58,720
[Since she turned you into a demon,]

111
00:04:59,199 --> 00:05:01,879
[why don't you enter her dream]

112
00:05:01,879 --> 00:05:03,040
[and find out the truth?]

113
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,160
[What exactly happened between us?]

114
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:12,000
[I must find out today.]

115
00:05:33,399 --> 00:05:34,319
My name is Meng Li.

116
00:05:34,399 --> 00:05:35,600
You can also call me Li.

117
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:36,879
What's your name?

118
00:05:37,199 --> 00:05:38,360
You're a demon hunter too?

119
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:39,160
Get out of here!

120
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:49,279
[How can this demon hunter]

121
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:51,639
[why does he look exactly like me?]

122
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:57,319
[And why does he sound like me?]

123
00:06:04,199 --> 00:06:05,199
[Hope you can]

124
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,560
[escape tomorrow.]

125
00:06:32,959 --> 00:06:33,759
Senior,

126
00:06:33,879 --> 00:06:35,000
did you see that demon?

127
00:06:36,079 --> 00:06:36,839
It ran that way.

128
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:37,560
After it!

129
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:39,439
Hurry!

130
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:48,079
Why did you save me?

131
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:50,439
Little demons like you

132
00:06:50,839 --> 00:06:52,639
taste best when raised.

133
00:06:53,160 --> 00:06:54,600
You eat demons?

134
00:06:54,839 --> 00:06:55,879
I didn't

135
00:06:55,879 --> 00:06:56,959
used to,

136
00:06:57,199 --> 00:06:59,240
but some short-lived demons

137
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:00,879
forget me so quickly.

138
00:07:01,319 --> 00:07:02,199
This time,

139
00:07:02,519 --> 00:07:03,240
I'll let it slide.

140
00:07:03,839 --> 00:07:05,480
But if it happens again,

141
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:06,959
I'll really eat them.

142
00:07:11,519 --> 00:07:13,839
[I hope to see you tomorrow.]

143
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:17,040
[Better yet, every day.]

144
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:19,560
[If only I could see you forever,]

145
00:07:20,439 --> 00:07:21,279
that would be even better.

146
00:07:23,319 --> 00:07:24,120
Daozhi,

147
00:07:24,519 --> 00:07:25,319
how did it go?

148
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:27,439
Did your master agree to our marriage?

149
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:28,720
Yes,

150
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:30,079
he did.

151
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:33,360
Really?

152
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:34,720
That's wonderful!

153
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:36,600
From this moment on,

154
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:38,279
we'll be together until old age,

155
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:40,959
through thick and thin.

156
00:07:41,519 --> 00:07:42,519
Together until old age,

157
00:07:43,199 --> 00:07:44,399
till death do us part.

158
00:08:06,240 --> 00:08:07,279
Meng Li,

159
00:08:07,399 --> 00:08:11,120
see you in the next life.

160
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:18,879
You remembered

161
00:08:20,959 --> 00:08:22,120
everything from a hundred years ago?

162
00:08:24,519 --> 00:08:26,000
No matter how many times we reincarnate,

163
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:29,800
I will still love you.

164
00:08:33,199 --> 00:08:34,120
The moon is lonely,

165
00:08:34,720 --> 00:08:35,919
the wind rises again,

166
00:08:36,679 --> 00:08:38,320
apricot flowers are scarce.

167
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:41,000
Thinking of the past,

168
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:42,320
it seems like a dream.

169
00:08:43,559 --> 00:08:44,840
♪ Tears silently fall ♪

170
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:47,600
♪ Tears silently fall ♪

171
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:49,240
Shen Que,

172
00:08:49,679 --> 00:08:51,279
have you remembered everything?

173
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:53,039
♪ Recalling the past ♪

174
00:08:53,039 --> 00:08:54,120
♪ Seems like a dream ♪

175
00:08:54,639 --> 00:08:56,759
She and I shared such a history?

176
00:08:57,360 --> 00:09:00,080
If you kill the witch who turned you into a demon,

177
00:09:00,679 --> 00:09:01,919
the sorcery can be undone,

178
00:09:02,519 --> 00:09:04,440
and you'll return to a mortal form.

179
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:06,559
Is the only way

180
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:09,240
to break the curse to kill my beloved?

181
00:09:11,519 --> 00:09:13,279
I'm very pleased

182
00:09:13,279 --> 00:09:14,960
with your rewritten story.

183
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:16,799
I keep my word.

184
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:18,919
What would you like to know?

185
00:09:19,039 --> 00:09:20,000
Please tell me

186
00:09:20,279 --> 00:09:21,840
where the Water Cloud Rhinoceros is.

187
00:09:24,039 --> 00:09:26,840
It's been a long time since anyone mentioned it.

188
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:29,399
Back then,

189
00:09:29,799 --> 00:09:31,679
the Great Demon shattered the Red Heart,

190
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:34,080
hiding the most important piece,

191
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:36,120
the Soul Fragment Water Cloud Rhinoceros.

192
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:37,559
He specifically ordered me

193
00:09:37,679 --> 00:09:39,240
to record its whereabouts

194
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:41,120
and the method to destroy it.

195
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:43,639
I even composed

196
00:09:43,919 --> 00:09:45,600
a poem about it.

197
00:09:56,840 --> 00:09:59,799
"Clouds and streams hide the beast's trace;

198
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:03,120
clouds and waters echo its grace.

199
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:06,360
Ten thousand spirits dwell in dark lair;

200
00:10:06,879 --> 00:10:10,279
where faint light glows, the sacred beast waits.

201
00:10:10,799 --> 00:10:12,559
Shattered dreams, lingering affection;

202
00:10:12,559 --> 00:10:13,879
heaven and earth overturned;

203
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:17,799
Profound Amber sinks into abyss, the calamity ends."

204
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:21,159
Senior,

205
00:10:21,159 --> 00:10:22,440
what does this poem mean?

206
00:10:22,799 --> 00:10:25,039
I was very talented at that time,

207
00:10:25,240 --> 00:10:26,279
and I wrote this poem.

208
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:28,000
I thought I was the best in the world.

209
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:30,759
Now a hundred years have passed,

210
00:10:30,879 --> 00:10:32,879
and I have forgotten it.

211
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:35,879
You have to figure it out yourself.

212
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:43,559
Well, it's done.

213
00:10:43,879 --> 00:10:45,480
I have finished the masterpiece.

214
00:10:46,159 --> 00:10:47,840
I have told you

215
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:49,240
everything Meng Li studied.

216
00:10:49,240 --> 00:10:50,840
You can leave now.

217
00:10:50,840 --> 00:10:51,240
Ah.

218
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:51,840
Let's go.

219
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:52,440
Meng Li,

220
00:10:54,879 --> 00:10:56,080
in your dream,

221
00:10:58,120 --> 00:10:59,960
I seemed to see everything from the past.

222
00:11:09,879 --> 00:11:10,919
Sceneries in dreams

223
00:11:11,720 --> 00:11:13,000
are hard to distinguish from reality.

224
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:15,240
They are unreliable.

225
00:11:24,399 --> 00:11:25,279
Young man,

226
00:11:25,759 --> 00:11:27,559
although you didn't help me,

227
00:11:27,639 --> 00:11:29,159
I'm in a good mood today.

228
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:31,080
I'll kindly remind you that

229
00:11:31,799 --> 00:11:34,320
You've been cursed.

230
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:35,879
Once it takes effect,

231
00:11:35,879 --> 00:11:36,679
it's devastating,

232
00:11:36,679 --> 00:11:37,759
harming the innocent

233
00:11:37,759 --> 00:11:38,840
and yourself.

234
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:41,200
You must be careful.

235
00:11:41,759 --> 00:11:42,759
What do you mean?

236
00:11:43,159 --> 00:11:43,960
Ah,

237
00:11:44,759 --> 00:11:46,879
if I tell you everything,

238
00:11:46,879 --> 00:11:48,399
it would lose its charm.

239
00:11:48,559 --> 00:11:49,840
You'll have to figure it out yourself.

240
00:11:51,799 --> 00:11:52,440
Thank you.

241
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:07,399
Meng Li.

242
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:08,919
Meng Li.

243
00:12:09,440 --> 00:12:10,840
Your Highness, why haven't you left?

244
00:12:11,360 --> 00:12:12,039
Are you unwilling

245
00:12:12,039 --> 00:12:13,639
to take this opportunity to kill me,

246
00:12:13,720 --> 00:12:15,440
or do you have some other plot waiting for me?

247
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:19,240
I'm just like you,

248
00:12:19,799 --> 00:12:21,159
with something yet to be investigated.

249
00:12:21,759 --> 00:12:22,759
The past

250
00:12:23,399 --> 00:12:24,799
in the dream I just mentioned,

251
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:27,519
I will also investigate it personally.

252
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:31,200
Farewell.
